      "rationale": "NIH is the primary regulatory QoI per FDA guidance on blood-contacting devices. Scalar shear stress and exposure time are intermediate QoIs feeding the power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen et al. 1990, modified Zhang). Direct mapping from CFD QoI to RH acceptance criterion documented in the COU and validated against bench data. Relevance chain complete."
    },
